# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# atelier-dashboard environment template
#
# Copy to `.env.local` (gitignored) and adjust for local development.
# Only PUBLIC, non-secret, operator-facing flags belong in this template.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# NEXT_PUBLIC_A2UI_RENDER — Governed A2UI render path (ADR-0024).
#
#   Owner        : Daniel Manzela
#   Introduced   : 2026-06-02 (ADR-0024 §1, feature-flag lifecycle table)
#   Default      : 0  (the hand-built React DesignSystemPanel renders; the
#                      A2UI payload is still captured on the `complete` SSE
#                      event but stays inert — fail-soft fallback path)
#   When 1       : the AT-044 design-system surface renders through
#                  @a2ui/react against the Atelier custom catalog
#                  (data-testid="studio-a2ui-design-system"); on any
#                  non-renderable / gate-rejected payload it FAILS SOFT back
#                  to the hand-built panel (data-testid="ds-panel").
#
#   BUILD-TIME-INLINE CAVEAT: Next.js statically inlines every NEXT_PUBLIC_*
#   variable at BUILD time (read at StudioClientShell via
#   `process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_A2UI_RENDER === '1'`). Flipping this value
#   therefore requires a REBUILD (`npm run build`), not just a server restart.
#   Setting it in a running process has no effect on the served bundle.
#
#   FLIP-ON CRITERIA (promote default 0 → 1): both must be green —
#     1. G2 fail-closed gate-before-emit governs the rendered surface, and
#     2. G3 a11y axe-in-CI assertion passes on the A2UI subtree.
#
#   CI NOTE: both flag states are exercised by the `dashboard-e2e` job, which
#   runs as a matrix over a2ui_flag: [off, on] (.github/workflows/ci.yml).
#   The flag-ON leg builds with NEXT_PUBLIC_A2UI_RENDER=1 so the A2UI render
#   path (and its axe assertion) actually executes; the flag-OFF leg proves
#   the hand-built fallback. The `a2ui-skew` job separately guards the
#   @a2ui/web_core 0.9.2/0.10.0 version bridge this render path depends on.
NEXT_PUBLIC_A2UI_RENDER=0
